The Health Department has recorded 998 new COVID-19 cases, taking the number of total infections to 1 505 586 in the last 24 hours. There have been a further 263 COVID-19 related deaths in the country, bringing the national death toll to 49 413. In a statement, Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize says most of the new deaths were recorded in KwaZulu-Natal. “Regrettably, we report 263 more COVID-19 related deaths: 51 from Eastern Cape, 27 from the Free State, 39 from Gauteng, 60 from KwaZulu-Natal, 55 from Limpopo, 0 from Mpumalanga, 0 from North West, 3 from Northern Cape and 28 from the Western Cape,” says Dr Mkhize. The cumulative total number of tests conducted to date is 8 932 950. The total number of recoveries stands at 1 419 459. As of today, the total number of confirmed #COVID19 cases is 1 505 586 the total number of deaths is 49 413, the total number of recoveries is 1 419 459 and the total number of vaccines administered is 32 315. pic.twitter.com/KqY3zJDnMw — Dr Zweli Mkhize (@DrZweliMkhize) February 23, 2021 